## M22: raw `%x` access inside a `raw` block is allowed.
##
## Per GPT-5.5 entry 35 (M21 design) + entry 38 (M22 cleanup):
## the `raw` block is the statement-level audit boundary for
## unsafe operations. Renamed from M19's `unsafe` keyword for
## sigil-alignment with the existing `%x` raw-prefix sigil
## (3 letters; reads as a noun; less Rust-imported).

sub main()
  x = 7
  raw
    r = %x         # `(raw x)` — raw access, requires raw block
    print(r)
